[Patient] What foods can I eat to help manage my heart failure? 
[Educator] Focus on lean proteins like chicken and fish for heart health. 

[Patient] Are there any specific fruits and vegetables I should include in my diet? 
[Educator] Berries, leafy greens, and colorful veggies are great for heart health. 

[Patient] Can I still enjoy some sweets or desserts in moderation? 
[Educator] Limit sweets and opt for healthier dessert options like fruit or yogurt. 

[Patient] How about drinks? What should I avoid or include in my diet? 
[Educator] Stay hydrated with water and limit sugary drinks like soda and juice. 

[Patient] Are there any specific spices or seasonings that are good for heart health? 
[Educator] Use herbs and spices like garlic, turmeric, and cinnamon for flavor and heart benefits.